        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 3 at 4:11PM PDT by NWS Pendleton OR</headline>
        <description>At 411 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles northwest of Granite, or 36 miles northeast of John Day, moving
northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northeastern Grant
County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
